<!--<h4>271.</h4>-->

<p><hi rend="italic">Slab built into the right wall of the gate leading to cave No. III.</hi></p>

<p>
<lb n="0"/>śrīyaśamantan
</p>

<!--<h4>272.</h4>-->

<p><hi rend="italic">Slab built into the Left Wall.</hi></p>

<p>
<lb n="1"/>śrīseṅkapayveyara mānaśikhedharmmarājan vikrantaraśi
<lb n="2"/>muruḷan
</p>

<!--<h4>273.</h4>-->

<p><hi rend="italic">Outer rock wall to the right of the above cave.</hi></p>

<p>
<lb n="0"/>śrī koṭṭalan
</p>

<!--<h4>274-275.</h4>-->

<p>These two inscriptions are engraved in shell characters.</p>

<!--<h4>276. (<hi rend="italic">B.K. No. 35 of 1938-39.</hi>) MAHĀKŪṬA, BADAMI TALUK, BIJAPUR DISTRICT.</h4>-->

<p><hi rend="italic">Pillar in the Saṅgamēs11vara temple in the compound of Mahākūṭēśvara temple.</hi></p>

<!--<h4>7th Century A.D.</h4>-->

<p>This record, in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">7th century A.D.,</hi> contains the name of an individual. <hi rend="italic">Cf.</hi> No. 257 above.</p>

<p>
<lb n="0"/>śrī nāḻpaya<unclear>n</unclear>
</p>

